deck_description:
Dopo il primo episodio, il deck è già migliorato molto, con l'aggiunta di carte come Sangan, Melffy Pony, Ovyraptor e FanFan! Soprattutto, quasi tutte le carte completamente inutili sono state eliminate, ed è già un ottimo passo in avanti rispetto all'inizio. 

Trovare FanFan per l'Extra Deck è una manna dal cielo, poiché abbiamo già due livello 6 che si specialano abbastanza facilmente. 

Ovviamente non può ancora essere definito un buon deck, ma siamo sulla strada giusta! 

 

After the first episode, the deck already got much better, with the inclusion of powerful cards such as Sangan, Melffy Pony, Ovyraptor and FanFan! Maybe even more important than that, we managed to take out all the completely useless cards, which is a great accomplishment in itself. 

Pulling FanFan for the Extra Deck has been a blessing, thanks to the two level 6 that we already have and that can special summon themselves. 

All in all, it's not a good deck yet, but a step in the right direction! 
The YouTube video is in italian, enjoy our Masochist Challenge!

yoloooooooo

I will be completely real when I say that Yubel as an archetype with its support from PHNI and LEDE is a lot more playable than Ashened is. And that is why you are seeing this Yubel Prediction Princess Deck from me and not an Ashened Prediction Princess list just yet. Yubel had a Level 9 monster revealed for its archetype recently in Phantom of Yubel which is a Level 9 DARK Fiend Fusion Monster that requires a Yubel monster and a Fiend monster with 0 ATK and DEF as Fusion Material and it must be Special Summoned from your Extra Deck by shuffling those materials from your hand, field, and/or GY into the Deck and/or Extra Deck. It cannot be destroyed by battle and you take no battle damage from battles involving it. And when your opponent activates a monster effect, you can Quick Effect Tribute it in order to change that effect to “Your opponent destroys 1 Yubel monster in their hand, Deck, or field. This is just an incredible card for Yubel, giving the archetype more ways to play and interact on your opponent’s turn and it is very easily Summonable considering the archetype only consists of Yubel monsters and 0 ATK/0 DEF Fiends. With the release of Nightmare Throne in LEDE, I believe that this Deck is very competent in getting you through both your Yubel combo, getting you to the Level 9 Phantom of Yubel, and transitioning to a full Prediction Princess combo. Full combo is World Legacy Monstrosity and any way to Samsara D Lotus. Normal Lotus and Tribute it to Special Summon Spirit of Yubel from Deck. Spirit of Yubel sets Eternal Favorite from your Deck to your Spell/Trap Zone. Shuffle Spirit of Yubel from field and Samsara D Lotus from GY into the Deck to Special Summon Phantom of Yubel from Extra Deck. Now just activate Monstrosity targeting it to Special Summon Prediction Princess Bibliomuse and Deus-X Krawler from Deck for Rank 9 access for Mereologic Aggregator, giving you full Prediction Princess combo. But what if you want to keep Phantom of Yubel on field as interruption and also to make use of Eternal Favorite on your opponent’s turn? Well, that would mean that we would need to Xyz using Bibliomuse and Deus-X rather than Deus-X and Phantom of Yubel. I have taken this into account which is why we are also playing Pre-Preparation of Rites and Prediction Ritual. Either you search what you would’ve searched off Bibliomuse off of Pre-Prep instead or you just hard draw a Bibliomuse to begin with or you open Instant Fusion for Master of Ham to get Bibliomuse from Deck. That would allow you to keep Phantom of Yubel on field to fade a monster effect and pop Spirit of Yubel in Deck to float into a Yubel from Deck, turning on Eternal Favorite to be able to Super Poly the board and go into Yubel - The Loving Defender Forever. I think that the Yubel support is all incredibly neat and very playable (surprisingly), but when I see a Level 9, you know what I gotta do.

For the monsters: 3 Prediction Princess Tarotrei, 1 Prediction Princess Tarotreith, and 3 Prediction Princess Bibliomuse. Tarotrei is a Quick Effect to flip a monster face-up or face-down and during the End Phase, she can Special Summon a Flip Monster from hand or GY face-down. Tarotreith can either be Ritual Summoned or Special Summoned via Tarotrei’s End Phase effect. On flip, she can Special Summon a Flip Monster from your Deck face-down and she can Quick Effect flip any number of your monsters either face-up or face-down. Bibliomuse can Special Summon herself back from GY face-down if she was tributed and sent there. On flip, she can add a Prediction Princess monster other than herself and a Ritual Spell from Deck to hand, and while she’s face-up on field, your Ritual Monsters gain targeting and destruction protection from your opponent’s effects. 2 Deus-X Krawler which negates all activated monster effects on your opponent’s side of the field after it has been flipped face-up and if it is destroyed on field, you can search for a Level 9 monster with a different Type and Attribute than it from Deck. 1 Yubel which we aren’t really using for its effect, but as a Summon off of Spirit of Yubel which would turn on the effect to Fusion Summon using either field with Eternal Favorite. 2 Spirit of Yubel who we are using for 2 things. On Special Summon, you can add to your hand or set a Spell/Trap that mentions Yubel from Deck. I don’t know why it also adds. It’s not like the archetype has a Quick-Play Spell that you would need to add to your hand instead of setting to activate. Just makes this effect able to be Ashed. And the other thing that we are using her for is Special Summoning a Yubel that is banished or in your hand, Deck, or GY on destruction. Again, we are popping her with Phantom of Yubel while in Deck to get Yubel onto field to turn on Eternal Favorite. We only need 2 because we just need to ensure we have a copy in Deck. No need to play 3. This is Prediction Princess, not pure Yubel. 3 Samsara D Lotus which Tributes itself to Special Summon a Yubel monster from Deck. That is pretty much all that we are using it for. It has other effects that may come up in some situations, but we are almost never going to be getting into those situations to actually make use of Lotus. This is the card that gives us access to our whole Yubel side of our Deck’s combo. We are already playing 3 copies of it along with 3 Nightmare Throne, the 1 Terraforming, and 3 Pot of Prosperity, so we have plenty of ways to access it. We are not playing Infernal Grave Squirmer despite it being a good card in Yubel because it is much better in a Deck more centralized around Yubel as the main focal point of the Deck rather than Yubel as an engine. But I’ll probably test it with Lady of Lament and Terrors of the Afterroot.

Spell/Traps: 3 Pre-Preparation of Rites. 2 Prediction Ritual which Specifically Ritual Summons Tarotrei and you can banish it from GY except the turn it was sent there in order to search for a Prediction Princess monster. 3 Underworld Ritual of Prediction which Ritual Summons a PRediction Princess Ritual Monster from your hand or GY face-up or face-down and you can banish it from GY during the Standby Phase to Special Summon a non-Ritual Prediction Princess monster from your Deck face-down. 3 Pot of Prosperity. 3 Nightmare Throne which, on activation, adds a Fiend monster with 0 ATK and 0 DEF from your Deck and either adds it to your hand or destroys it. And once per turn, if a face-up Yubel monster(s) you control leaves the field by a card effect, you can add a Yubel monster that is banished or in Deck or GY whose original Level is 1 higher or 1 lower than the Level of 1 of the monsters that left the field had and then you can Special Summon it ignoring its Summoning Conditions. If anything, we are just using Nightmare Throne to search. Yes, we could theoretically make use of its other effect, but since we aren’t playing an actual Yubel Deck with Terror Incarnate and Ultimate Nightmare, this effect really doesn’t do much for us, so it is best not to worry yourself with trying to play in accordance to that effect. 1 Terraforming. 1 Instant Fusion for Master of Ham. 3 World Legacy Monstrosity which either Special Summons a Level 9 monster from your hand or targets a Level 9 monster you control to Special Summon 2 Level 9 monsters from your Deck with a different Type and Attribute than that monster but with different names. 1 Called By the Grave and 1 Harpie’s Feather Duster. 3 Infinite Impermanence and 1 Eternal Favorite. Eternal Favorite is a Continuous Trap that can once per turn either Special Summon a Yubel monster from banishment or GY (with neither player being able to respond to the Summon) or if you control Yubel, you can discard a card and send Eternal Favorite to GY to Fusion Summon using monsters from either field including a Yubel monster. I was planning on playing Nightmare Pain also as a way to potentially search for some form of follow-up for your Yubel stuff, but I just felt like Eternal Favorite just did way more.

Extra Deck: 1 Yubel - The Loving Defender Forever which requires a Yubel monster and 1 or more Effect Monsters as Fusion Material and if it is Fusion Summoned, you can inflict 500 damage to your opponent for each material used for its Summon. IT cannot be destroyed by battle or card effect and you take no battle damage from battles involving it. And it has an effect similar to Ultimate Nightmare where at the end of the Damage Step, if it battled an opponent’s monster, you inflict damage to your opponent equal to that monster’s ATk and then banish that monster. This card is just a great card to go into with Super Poly-esque effects like that of Eternal Favorite and considering that it needs a Yubel monster and 1 or more Effect Monsters as material, it can easily Fuse away your opponent’s whole board. 2 Phantom of Yubel. I thought about playing just the 1 copy of it at first, but it is practically a contact fusion of sorts and is really easily Summonable. Considering that we are more than likely able to get the right monsters into rotation to Summon it again on turn 3, I feel like playing the second copy gives you more assurance against your opponent’s monster effects on turn 3 and also gives you a Level 9 to work with as well. 1 Garura, Wings of Resonant Life and 1 Mudragon of the Swamp as Super Poly targets. And it is also important to mention that you just need to use a Yubel monster as Fusion Material when Fusion Summoning using Eternal Favorite. You are not locked into Yubel Fusions, so under certain instances, you could possibly go for either Mudragon or Garura if you want to make use of their effects - Garura drawing 1 if sent to GY or Mudragon being able to change its Attribute and make monsters on the field with the same Attribute be untargetable. 1 Master of Ham which Special Summons a Flip Monster from hand or Deck face-down on Fusion Summon. 2 Herald of the Arc Light which searches for a Ritual Monster or Ritual Spell if sent to GY. 2 Mereologic Aggregator, 1 Laevateinn, Generaider Boss of Shadows, and 1 Jormungandr, Generaider Boss of Eternity. 1 S:P Little Knight, 1 I:P Masquerena, and 1 Gravity Controller.

Side Deck: 3 Nibiru, the Primal Being, 3 Thunder King, the Lightningstrike Kaiju, 2 Gizmek Kaku, the Supreme Shining Sky Stag, 2 Cosmic Cyclone, 2 Super Polymerization, and 3 Evenly Matched.

deck_excerpt: Read description for information on the casual fan-made Reborn Format.
deck_description:
The official Yu-Gi-Oh Banlist applies to this format. 

Altered Rules: 

1. Fusion, Xyz, Synchro, Link, and Pendulum Monsters can only be Special Summoned from the Extra Deck to an Extra Monster Zone, or a Main Monster Zone a Link Monster Points to. 

2. The turn player can only use one Extra Monster Zone per turn. Once they have used one, they cannot use the other one until the end of their turn. 

3. The turn player can conduct two Normal Summons/Sets; one in Main Phase 1, and one in Main Phase 2. 

4. The first turn player does not skip their draw during the first Draw Phase. 

5. Main deck limit is 40 to 50 cards. 

6. Extra Deck and Side Deck limit is 10. 

7. Players can only use one card per copy in their Main and Extra Deck with exceptions based on choosing one of the following builds (non-effect monsters do not count against this limit): 

- You can have one Forbidden Card in your deck, as well as 2 or 3 copies of one card of your choosing. 

- You can have 3 copies of two cards of your choosing. 

- You can have 2 copies of three cards of your choosing.

Important combos you need to keep in mind:
1. With Harvester only: Summon Harvester to add a Brutal Dozer (or Roadroller IF you already have Dozer in your hand). Tribute Harvester for Dozer, then summon Trencher. Overlay to River Stormer, detach Trencher to add Therion "King" Regulus (or any Level 10 trains if you have at least 1 of them or already have Regulus). The rest is up to you.

2. With Gearframe: Summon Gearframe to add Unclaspare. Summon Unclaspare when you add it to your hand then activate it to send either Ruinforce, Citadel, or Fortress (if you have either Level 10 Machina monsters in your hand, so you could discard them). Then Link into Plat Gadget (or Xyz into Gear Gigant if you have summoned Fortress). If you summoned GGX but don't have a Harvester, add it. If you only Linked into Plat Gadget, activate it's effect to summon harvester from your hand and do the harvester combo. The rest is up to you!

deck_excerpt: Control your opponent from special summoning and using the graveyard. Shuts down most decks and is fun to watch them quit the match.
deck_description: With this deck, you really want to go first. If you can get Necrovalley on the field and hit your oppenent with a royal tribute on the 1st turn, they pretty much are screwed, depending on deck honestly. My rule of thumb is to always keep necrovalley on the field. Getting Hidden Temples on the field is also huge, to stop oppenent from special summoning in general, which shuts down many decks. Getting Supernatuaralist on the field is huge too, grabbing any gravekeeper card you need. Play the x3 Torrential and x3 Judgement to keep yourslef in the game if you don't get the right draw right off the bat. I love the Ash Blossom for when I don't get to go 1st, try to limit what's on the field. The only monster I really use from the extra deck is the Supernaturalist, but you can play around with that. I use high ATK monsters for Dogmatika.

deck_name: Voiceless Voice Branded Post LEDE Guide
deck_excerpt: Post Legacy Of Destruction Voiceless Voice Guide.
deck_description:
Voiceless Voice Branded Post LEDE

Welcome back to a update guide for the new archetype Voiceless Voice post Legacy Of Destruction©.

This is a branded variant with some spice so i want to tell you some combos and lines about it.

(this is part 2 aka the updated guide part for the older guide without the new cards.)

I will try to cover everything in this guide now also the main cards and the main combo.

Main Monster

 

  

Lo, the Prayers of the Voiceless Voice 

- on NS/SS search and places a Voiceles Voice spell or trap

- if a ritual monster is SS and she is in the grave, she can SS herself to the field once per turn

 

 

 

Saffira, Dragon Queen of the Voiceless Voice 

- discard from hand to dump the ritual spell from deck to the GY and searches aus a light warrior/dragon ritual monster

- can banish itself to ritual summon a light warrior/dragon ritual monster

 

 

 

 

Sauravis, Dragon Sage of the Voiceless Voice 

- on effect activation he can bounce himself back to hand and SS a ritual sauravis from deck to the field

- he can SS himself by shuffling 2 spells including a ritual spell back into the deck

 

 

 

Skull Guardian, Protector of the Voiceless Voice 

- on his ritual summon he searches us a voiceless voice or ritual warrior/dragon monster to the hand

- if lo is on the field he gets an omni negate with destroy and 2050 atk boost (no omni negate if Lo is only in GY)

 

 

 

Barrier of the Voiceless Voice 

- adds you a Voiceless Voice card or "Skull Guardian" ritual monster

- Lo & a light ritual monster on the field gives you target protection for light monsters and he can only attack ritual monster

 

 

 

Prayers of the Voiceless Voice 

- can be used for rirual summon any light ritual monster

- if a light ritual monster leaves the field you can banish this card and SS a Skull Guardian/Sauravis or Saffira Ritual from your deck

 

 

 

Radiance of the Voiceless Voice 

- shuffle a light ritual monster or ritual spell from GY or hand into the deck & add/SS a voiceless voice monster from your deck

- you can target cards on the opponents field up to the number of diffrent ritual monster you control destroy them also this card

 

 

 

New Cards

 

 

Blessing of the Voiceless Voice 

- target 1 Voiceless Voice card in your GY/Banished Zone and add it back to the hand

- if a non-ritual monster is NS/SS you can ritual summon a light warrior/dragon monster from your hand (the monster cannot be     destroyed by battle)

 

 

 

Saffira, Dragon Deity of the Voiceless Voice 

- if this card is ritual summoned & you have Lo on the field/GY you can draw 2 cards then discard 1

- when a attack is declared against a ritual monster you can rip your opponent 1 card in his hand

- during opponents end phase you can add a light monster from your GY to your hand

 

Main Combo

Lo Way: NS Lo, the Prayers of the Voiceless Voice place Barrier of the Voiceless Voice search Saffira, Dragon Queen of the Voiceless Voice dump Saffira, Dragon Queen of the Voiceless Voice & Prayers of the Voiceless Voice (from the deck) search Skull Guardian, Protector of the Voiceless Voice banish Saffira, Dragon Queen of the Voiceless Voice use Lo, the Prayers of the Voiceless Voice as ritual tribute material RS Skull Guardian, Protector of the Voiceless Voice chain 1 Skull Guardian, Protector of the Voiceless Voice chain 2 Lo, the Prayers of the Voiceless Voice SS Lo, the Prayers of the Voiceless Voice to the field & search a Saffira, Dragon Queen of the Voiceless Voice .

 

Diviner Way: NS Diviner of the Herald dump Trias Hierarchia tribute Diviner of the Herald with Trias Hierarchia effect. In GY effect Diviner of the Herald to SS Lo, the Prayers of the Voiceless Voice place Barrier of the Voiceless Voice search Saffira, Dragon Queen of the Voiceless Voice dump Saffira, Dragon Queen of the Voiceless Voice & Prayers of the Voiceless Voice (from the deck) search Skull Guardian, Protector of the Voiceless Voice banish Saffira, Dragon Queen of the Voiceless Voice use Lo, the Prayers of the Voiceless Voice as ritual tribute material RS Skull Guardian, Protector of the Voiceless Voice chain 1 Skull Guardian, Protector of the Voiceless Voice chain 2 Lo, the Prayers of the Voiceless Voice SS Lo, the Prayers of the Voiceless Voice to the field & search a Saffira, Dragon Queen of the Voiceless Voice .

 

 

Boardbreaker

Nearly every Voiceless Voice list is playing like 9 up to 15 handtraps i mean ok it's a handtrap format but in this case literally everyone is not prepared for some nice boardbreaker. We play some good going second cards like: Forbidden Droplet , Evenly Matched or Super Polymerization .

Another good card is Triple Tactics Thrust . It allows us to basiclly search all of our spell/trap cards so we have access to other tech cards like Ultimate Slayer , Soul Release , The Black Goat Laughs , Different Dimension Ground  or Summon Limit .

Extra Deck Monsters 

We have a variety of tech stuff aviable in our extra deck.

Let's cover Albion the Sanctifire Dragon .

This card is our key piece for the Jowgen the Spiritualist lock if we loose the first round.

By using Branded Fusion and sending Fallen of Albaz & Jowgen the Spiritualist we can summon Albion the Sanctifire Dragon .

Now in the enemy turn we trigger his effect to special summon jowgen from the GY to our field to lock the opponent out of special summoning what in the most chases is an isntant turn skip but don't try that against Floowandereeze because they can tribute Jowgen the Spiritualist for a normal summon.

The next card we will cover is Branded Fusion and it's opportunities they give us.

We can use Fallen of Albaz & Saffira, Dragon Queen of the Voiceless Voice to fusion summon Albion the Branded Dragon then we can use him to got into Mirrorjade the Iceblade Dragon or the combo even further with Lubellion the Searing Dragon by discarding 1 card we can shuffle back our banished Fallen of Albaz & Lubellion the Searing Dragon for Mirrorjade the Iceblade Dragon . After we have done this line we still have Albion the Branded Dragon in the grave and we can trigger his effect to search another Branded Fusion to go into Albion the Sanctifire Dragon .

(in addition): i will maybe add one copy of Branded in Red as a alternative search target for Albion the Branded Dragon . we could use Branded in Red to go into a Guardian Chimera but that's only speculation at the moment so maybe i will add it at some time.

The other extra deck monster are mainly for Super Polymerization or as a sending target for Ultimate Slayer .

For time options we can use Condemned Darklord . She heals us at the end of the turn for 500LP for each fairy monster we control.

Siding Patterns

Siding patterns are very diverse to each match up.

Most of the time i will side out the Diviner of the Herald package with Trias Hierarchia and Forbidden Droplet to put in Jowgen the Spiritualist or Evenly Matched / Soul Release / Ultimate Slayer .

The Black Goat Laughs is mainly for kashtira match ups to call Kashtira Fenrir or Kashtira Unicorn .

Also the Summon Limit works fine with most of thee decks because we have a good time finding it in a handtrap heavy format with Triple Tactics Thrust in our deck.

End

We are now at the end of this guide and i hope that you have learned some stuff about this deck.

I will try to upload a new version after Light of Destruction got it's release in the TCG.

Then we can add some heavy consistency cards like Blessing of the Voiceless Voice & Saffira, Dragon Deity of the Voiceless Voice for banish recycle / ritualsummon and also some hand rip. 

So stay tuned what we can do with this deck in the near future.

Stay safe duelists and have fun.

XenoYGO

This is probably going to be the cheapest deck you can play. No extra deck and very interactive. I made it as budget-friendly as I could while remaining competitive. You can make upgrades to this deck over time. Like switching out the Monarchs erupt for skill drain to give you access to an extra deck, however, you will lose a monarch spell or trap to discard with Pantheism. This deck is so unique in the sense that you use a variety of micro-interactions to create a brand-new deck at a cheap price and play in completely different access to most decks. Kind of cool to get a bunch of scrapped-together cards to create such a unique list. Definitely can cheese some wins at your locals.

deck_excerpt: Diabellstar Snake-Eye Fire King  / Team YCS Las Vegas Top 16
deck_description:
Category: Tournament Meta Decks (TCG)

Tournament Meta Decks are current-level Meta Decks that are capable of going up against the best of the best. These are curated lists that cannot be uploaded by regular users.

Creator: Andrei Ativo

Tournament: Team YCS Las Vegas – February 24th 2024

Placement: Top 16

A variation of another deck I saw by BorkStudios, trying to make it more consistent.

The general line you can make in most games is going into the Gunkan Suship Shirauo-Class Carrier to search your Catch-of-the-Day, then make your Uni-class. The deck is a little jank, but Fire King adds a little additional power to the Suships, and the Fire King Island field spell means that your Gunkan Suships can't be destroyed by card effects while Shirauo-class is on the field.

deck_excerpt: In most cases, damage reflection hard counters tier 0 fire decks in Masterduel!
deck_description:
In most cases, damage reflection hard counters tier 0 fire decks in Masterduel! Your Mikanko monsters are summoned untargetable and indestructible due to the mechanics/nature of the deck, immediately rendering many interactions of the Snake-Eye cards useless!

CHEESE out wins consistently towards opponents who are consistently not ready to face kaijus, boardbreakers and untargetable, indestructible, battle-immune shrine maidens! Not only are these ladies beautiful, they're terrifyingly potent and they interact with opponent's boards in ways that most decks aren't ready for!

Check out my previous written guide on this deck from last year!

Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!

deck_description: Replays - https://youtu.be/-ws7wqyrsWs?feature=shared
Unchained Yubel (Mar 2024)

1) Use samurai combo to establish multiple summons and monsters,

2) Use fossil engile to get naturia beast ( use cross-sheep)

3)Sheep+ 1 monster = Promethean = Amblowhale

Final board = Baronne + Naturia Beast + Amblowhale (and more depending the hand)

 

This board translates into 1.Baronne negate (mostly the monster negate or if opponent goes into evenly) 2. Infinite spell negates with beast 3. If opponent goes into fenrir or into TY-PHON use Promethean to destroy it and win turn. 

Let's say u have then after the board somehow only promethean on board, use her revival for amblo or adamancipator leonite and ggs

-Tip. Try and get into rotation Leonite or even end board so you can revive on opp turn (raptite and with accel WIND you can use the 2nd effect) and destroy leonite and no Amblowhale so you can keep having resources.
Wouldn't let me add Arise-heart thats an essential card to have in it!

It's marik's deck from battle city.  This includes every card that he used.  Cards that don't exist are: Dark Protection and Zombie Jewel.  If you look online you may find more but many were renamed and I had to do some searching.  A card that apparently does exist but I can't find here is Card of Last Will. Add that to your deck if you want to.  Obivously When using this list you will need to add the Ra support with the deck.  That's the only way to get the full effects of Ra that made the card so powerful.  Which honestly steals away from this deck actually being able to do it's thing...torture.

deck_excerpt: Locks out fire decks and makes a decent board off a 1 card combo.
deck_description:
The point of the deck is to turbo out your Chaofeng and lock your opponent out of using Fire type monsters. However, using Denglong you can also lock your opponent out of any other type. It always locks lights, so once it hits the field you are insulated from Nibiru. A typical end board might look something like Chaofeng, S:P, Crocodragon, and Kashtira Fenrir. 

The deck might look awful, and maybe it is, but I think it has potential if you find a better secondary engine than Naturia. This was mostly constructed for fun, but holds up decently well in the current meta due to the high non engine count and the anti-fire strategy.

deck_name: Secondo Episodio Masochist Challenge di TheMentisGroup
deck_excerpt: Il Deck di fine secondo episodio per la Masochist Challenge di TheMentisGroup!
deck_description:
Abbiamo aggiunto al Deck alcune delle migliori carte che ci potevano capitare in questo episodio! Tra tutte, abbiamo Diabound Nucleo, Metalmorph e Squadra Ballista, e incredibilmente per noi è giocabile Roccia di Guerra Orpis! Continuiamo inoltre a provare la strategia con mostri Acqua per evocare il nostro "Boss" Monster Sirenide Abissmegalo, ma lasciamo a voi scoprire come è andata. 

In this episode we managed to pull some of the absolute best cards we could hope for a Masochist Challenge! Above all, Diabound Kernel, Metalmorph and Ballista Squad, but even War Rock Orpis is incredibly good for us! We are also still trying to push the Water strategy to summon our "Boss" Mermail Abyssmegalo, but we'll let you find out for yourself if it worked or not!

Usually called Rock Stun, You use powerful floodgate effects of Fossil Dyna/Barrier statue and play Koa'ki Meiru monsters as negation to protect your floodgate monsters. Moon Mirror Shield and armory call protect against any battle phase effects you might encounter. Ties of the Breathern can also allow you to get Fossil Dyna or Barrier statue from deck if you fail to open it. This deck really prefers going first if possible and in game two you can side easily into board breakers. Its much easier for people to play and has a very simplistic strategy for new or returning players.

Original (January 2024): https://ygoprodeck.com/deck/omni-heros-420976

Usually called Umi Control, this deck uses Kairyu-Shin's unique lockdown effect to win games. This deck can go first or second since based on its ruling can immediately boardwipe certain strategies with its ability. You can also use a small toolbox of tech cards to even out certain matchups. The "Sea Stealth" cards provide protection and the "Fury" cards provide removal, both Searchable with Kairyu Shin (This thing is practically a custom card). With Fish Sonar you also get a small toolbox of various water monsters to use in certain scenarios: Jellyfish is a generic negate, Kraken recurable pop/attack negate, and Barrier statue for another wall to get over for your opponent. If any of them are destroyed, they can return with Dark Reef. Sonar can summon any water-normal monster from the deck and the choice is really up to you for which one. I choose Salmon because it is level 5, which makes is normal summonable with Legendary Ocean. The main issue with this deck is that since Fish Sonar has one printing available it's still $10-12 dollars a copy, But if you're willing to spend a little extra for a fun locals deck I'd highly recommend it.

Floowandereeze was the last deck I played before basically leaving the game for good and It was for the longest time the most competitive deck I had played. Yes, everyone hated the barrier statue lock, but it was the same strategy that everyone else was playing at the time. I probably could have stayed a lot longer since Tear was becoming meta when I left but safe to say I was done with Yugioh for a while. It's just unfortunate that some of the only good budget decks to play at times are the ones most likely to be hated by the player base by design

Quick tangent aside, it's still a competent rogue deck. You won't get to barrier statue lock anymore, you still have access to a good variety of tools for a decent control deck (a lot like how Monarchs used to play). Avian is a generic negate, Snowl is an interruption, and Raiza is removal. Simorgh can potentially lock down your opponent's Spell/Traps with Anti-spell Fragrance and is occasionally recycled from the graveyard by banishing Dimension Shifters stuck in your hands. It is more bricky than it used to be, but it is still a fun local deck. The only other criticism I have is that you have to have an understanding of the chain link effects and chain blocking.

Another budget deck that is very beginner-friendly. You go second, wipe the board, and deal 8000+ damage for the game. If you're forced to go first you play Infintrack megaclops and sit on its invulnerable hide until you assemble lethal, but more than likely you're going for the Otk. Game 2 you side out your going second cards for floodgates depending on the matchup(What other deck can you say you sided in Slifer the Sky Dragon? It's easily summonable in this deck and backed up by floodgates you can easily steal some games with memories of hope.) The only con is how bricky it can be sometimes, and is very game-dependent on opening the Field spell or a way to search it. You have to win turn one, but it is a nice way to speed up gameplay so beginners don't have to stress out about going into time and keep the games running faster for your locals. Overall, very fun deck for such a low pricepoint, just be prepared for your opponents to get salty.

I find that these decks are not only incredibly cheap to play but also very beginner-friendly. Giving a new player a simple win condition and teaching them how to get to that win-con is very helpful in teaching new players. It also makes sideboarding not as difficult to explain to new players as some other decks. Most Otk decks are not very good at all going first, so most opponents intuitively will choose to go second game 2 and thus will give the new player an immediate understanding of what is put in their sideboard (Cards that both counter the metagame and are good to have going first). Since games wrap up in a couple of turns it means most beginners won't get stressed out over time rules and get them used to a more fast-paced gameplay than most other card games.

That tangent aside this deck is designed to Otk as efficiently as possible. The Yosenjus all have a double summon effect and as long as you have 2 in hand you can summon Utopia Double whose ability in tandem with either double or nothing hits for 10,000 damage or Utopia Beyond hitting for 6000 with its effect easily Otking through most monsters. If you lose access to double or nothing with Pot of Desires banish effect, the Kaiju engine and Alpha can easily to lvl 8s on board to summon Number 38: Draglubion whose eff brings out a Number 101: Numeron Dragon whose attack goes 9000 to finish the game that way. Everything is to help consistency (Pot of Desires/Trade-in) and every other card is different forms a removal. the win con is simple, wipe the opponent's board and hit for 8000+ damage for the win. This deck is adaptable, cheap, and very beginner-friendly to new players.
